biz.paluch.spinach.impl

Class HelloClusterSocketAddressSupplier

  • java.lang.Object
    • biz.paluch.spinach.impl.ClusterAwareNodeSupport
      • biz.paluch.spinach.impl.HelloClusterSocketAddressSupplier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConnectionAware, SocketAddressSupplier, Supplier<SocketAddress>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NodeIdAwareSocketAddressSupplier

    public class HelloClusterSocketAddressSupplier
extends ClusterAwareNodeSupport
implements SocketAddressSupplier, ConnectionAware
    Supplier for adresses that is aware of the cluster nodes.

    This class performs a HELLO command handshake upon connection and retrieves the nodes from the command result. The node set is not refreshed once it is retrieved. The nodes are used in the order of their priority in a round-robin fashion. Until the handshake is completed a fallback SocketAddressSupplier is used.

    Author:
    Mark Paluch
